snippet.textDisplay: In South Africa (my opinion only!), Sonata is more towards the larger car class. To me, the Accent is a large enough car. I was forced by a break down to fit 4 adults and a child,  with a weekend's luggage into mine for a return trip from camping. A tight fit, but reasonably comfortable. Every rear passenger (without exception) I have carried has commented on the more than ample space in the rear seat area. One would assume that our view here is skewed by the price of fuel (over 16 bucks a litre!, it costs like 700 SA bucks to fill up the  Accent), so bang for buck, or size, is pretty important to the average person. I must say though, having owned several old school Alfas, Fords and still having a Honda, Hyundai has really got their act together. For the price we pay, there is not much better value, if of course, you don't worry about wasting fuel or the old bug bear of prestige. Seriously, do you want to get from A to B or do you want to make a statement? How small is your penis actually? A comfortable, pleasant, economical (6l/100km or 39 mpg highway) car with a way better than average sound system is all you need.....taking shelter now from the flak coming my way! Nice review of a nice car, Doug!
